Package: Matisse
Title: Multi-modal Analysis of Transcript Isoforms in Single-Cell Sequencing Experiments
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("k3yavi", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "placeholder@example.com",
    comment = c(ORCID = ""))
Description: Integrative analysis of single-cell transcriptomics with isoform
    resolution. Matisse extends Seurat and Signac to support PSI (Percent Spliced
    In) matrix calculation, isoform-aware quality control, and visualization for
    long-read and splice-resolved single-cell RNA-seq data. It provides a
    dedicated S4 object that wraps a Seurat object, keeping gene expression and
    isoform layers synchronized throughout an analysis.
